🧠 What is Snowflake?

Snowflake is a cloud-based data warehouse that separates compute, storage, and services layers. It allows you to scale resources independently, pay only for what you use, and handle structured and semi-structured data efficiently.

Key Features

Elastic scalability – scale up or down instantly.

Separation of compute and storage – independent resource management.

Secure data sharing – share data across accounts without copying.

Multi-cloud support – available on AWS, Azure, and GCP.

🏗️ Snowflake Architecture Overview

Snowflake’s architecture consists of three layers:

Layer

Description

Storage Layer

Stores data in compressed, columnar format.

Compute Layer

Virtual warehouses perform queries and transformations.

Services Layer

Manages metadata, authentication, and optimization.

